  @doc """
  Executes a given command string using 'sh -c'.

  This function takes a single string representing the shell command
  and executes it. It returns the standard System.cmd/3 tuple:
  {:ok, output_string, error_string} on success (exit code 0),
  or {:error, output_string, error_string, exit_code} on failure (non-zero exit code).

  ## Examples

      iex> ShellExecutor.execute("echo hello")
